
[1]shovel

   SHOVEL, n. shov'l. An instrument consisting of a broad scoop or hollow
   blade with a handle; used por throwing earth or other loole substances.

   SHOVEL, v.t.

   1. To take up and throw with a shovel; as, to shovel earth into a heap
   or into a cart, or out of a pit.

   2. To gather in great quantities.
